The polarization curves of as-prepared PTEB nanostructured on titanium plate as photocathodes were performed using a three-electrode setup contains working electrode (PTEBs), counter electrode (Pt wire), and reference electrode (Ag/AgCl). The simulated sunlight was from a 200 W Xenon lamp (100 mW cm−2) coupled with an AM 1.5 G filter (Newport). An electrochemical analyzer (CHI 760 E) was applied to measure the LSV characteristic of the electrodes, with 1 mV s−1 scan rate, and there is no correction on data for any losses of uncompensated resistance. The electrolyte (0.01 M Na2SO4, pH = 6.8) was degassed for 30 min by flushing high purity argon at room temperature (ca. 25 °C) before the measurement. The EIS spectra were recorded by applying a 10 mV AC signal in the frequency range from 100 K to 0.01 Hz at a DC bias of 0.3 V vs. RHE (i.e. − 0.3 V vs. Ag/AgCl). Current density was calculated using the exposed geometric surface area of 1.0 cm2 of the photoelectrode1(Jphotocurrentdensity=Jmeasuredphotocurrent∕Sexposedgeometricsurfacearea)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
